description.narrative: The CO faced severe challenges in evidence generation during the emergency of COVID-19 and the explosions in Bata. However, UNICEF continued advocating to promote greater availability of reliable, timely, and disaggregated information on the situation of children, including a newnational household survey, and signed a work plan with the Ministry of Finance and Planning. The CO generated new evidence regarding WASH, learning outcomes in primary education, and the use of humanitarian cash transfers (HCT) by households affected by the explosions in Bata. With support from RO, UNICEF achieved progress with the regional-supported evaluations on immunization and birth registrations. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:25/01/2022
